# Palette

## Palette Theme

    ![Screenshot](../img/style/globalPalette.jpg)
    

Palette Themes can be set in the stylesheet properties. The Palette property
dropdown is automatically populated with these themes. If the Palette property
is updated then the colors in the Palettes will update based on set theme.

Defining Theme

To define a palette theme, add the following css template

  1. define palette name , must prefix with "palette_" e.g .palette_gradient

  2. define theme e.g .light or .dark

  3. define index name e.g .color1

sample css:

    
    
    .palette_gradient .light .color1 { color : #ff0000; }
    

## Palettes

    ![Screenshot](../img/style/palette.jpg)

For Color order for a [pivot query](../datasources/#pivot-query) or when using
a regular expression for a wild card property, the assignment of the colors is
done in the order of the Data.

